  "text": "This noise coming from quantum fluctuations, intrinsic to the initial state where each atom is in a superposition of a and b, is known in clocks as the \"partition noise\". The idea of spin squeezing [CITATION_1] is that the Heisenberg relation (4) allows to reduce ∆S y provided that ∆S z is increased. This idea is illustrated in Fig.1 . To quantify the spin squeezing we use the parameter ξ 2 introduced in [1]:",
